<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="separate-v">separate <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /'sepəreɪt/    美 /'sepəreɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(使) 分离；(使) 分开</strong></h4>
<p>to divide into different parts or groups：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>separate</strong> the <strong>eggs</strong> 
把蛋清和蛋黄分开</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The students were <strong>separated into</strong> four groups. 
学生被分成了4组。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>As we joined the big crowd I got <strong>separated from</strong> my friends. 
当我们走进一大群人中时，我跟朋友们走散了。</p><footer>2001 全国</footer></div>

<h3 id="divide-separate">辨析 divide, separate</h3>
<p>二者均可表示“分开”。<br />
<strong>divide</strong> 通常指把整体分为若干部分，其后常接介词 into。
<strong>separate</strong> 通常指把原来连在一起或靠近的东西分隔开来，其后常接介词 from。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We’d better <strong>separate</strong> the good ones <strong>from</strong> the bad ones.
我们最好把好的和坏的分开。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She doesn’t want to be <strong>separated from</strong> him.
她不想和他分开。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>把...隔开</strong></h4>
<p>to lie or stand between two countries, areas, etc., keeping them apart：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>England is <strong>separated from</strong> France by the Channel.
英国和法国之间隔着英吉利海峡。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>区分；分清：</strong></h4>
<p>to make sb / sth different in someway from sb / sth else：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The capacity to think <strong>separates</strong> humans <strong>from</strong> animals. 
思维能力使人有别于动物。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>分居；分手</strong></h4>
<p>to stop living together as a couple：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>separated from</strong> his wife after 7 years of marriage. 
他和妻子结婚7年后分居了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>separately /'sepərətli/ adv   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The little girl got <strong><em>_</em></strong>__ (分开) from the group in the dark.  </li>
<li>Hospital staff burst into cheers after doctors completed a 20-hour operation to have <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ one-year-old twins at the head.   </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. separated  2. separated  </p></div>